results.name: Number of rotational symmetries in the binary expansion of a number with 0 appended to the front.
link: Gary Doran, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100
example: a(0) = 2 because 00 has two rotational symmetries; a(21) = 3 because 010101 has 3 rotational symmetries.
